def: The warm-blooded vertebrates, comprising the mammals and birds;-- the antithesis to hematocrya.
A vertical iron bolt, by which the forward axle and wheels of avehicle or the trucks of a railroad car are connected with the otherparts.
An outer, or exterior. wall. See Vauntmure. [Obs.] Hakluyt.
In railroads, the bed or foundation on which the superstructure(ties, rails, etc.) rests; in common roads, the whole material laidin place and ready for travel.
A genus of cruciferous plants, containing the lady's-smock,cuckooflower, bitter cress, meadow cress, etc.
Of or pertaining to ulcers; as, an ulcerative process.
